  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Danish grant is given to support a 4-day Summer School on preventing torture and ill-treatment of female detainees through gender-sensitive monitoring. The course aims to increase the knowledge and capacity of existing and newly establishe NPMs in relation to the standards set out in the Bangkok Rules (UN Rules for the Treatment of Women Prisoners and Non-custodial Measures for Women Offenders). The summer school will be a pilot program with a view of duplicating the initiative in other regions. The course will be organised by Penal Reform Internation in partnership with University of Bristol Law School and the APT.

The objectives of the Summer School were agreed as: 1. An increased level of knowledge and skills for undertaking monitoring visits that are gender-sensitive; 2. Country-exchange of good practice in relation to gender-sensitive monitoring; 3. Networks built between NPMs.</narrative>
  </description>
